<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id121e29a9-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777" identifier="/us/usc/t44/s711"><num value="711">§ 711.</num><heading> Printing Acts, joint resolutions, and treaties</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Director of the Government Publishing Office, on receiving from the Archivist of the United States a copy of an Act or joint resolution, or from the Secretary of State, a copy of a treaty, shall print an accurate copy and transmit it in duplicate to the Archivist of the United States or to the Secretary of State, as the case may be, for revision. On the return of one of the revised duplicates, he shall make the marked corrections and print the number specified by <ref href="/us/usc/t44/s709">section 709 of this title</ref>.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id121e29aa-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">(<ref href="/us/pl/90/620">Pub. L. 90–620</ref>, <date date="1968-10-22">Oct. 22, 1968</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/82/1249">82 Stat. 1249</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/98/497/tI/s107/b/1">Pub. L. 98–497, title I, § 107(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1984-10-19">Oct. 19, 1984</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/98/2286">98 Stat. 2286</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/113/235/dH/tI/s1301/c/1">Pub. L. 113–235, div. H, title I, § 1301(c)(1)</ref>, <date date="2014-12-16">Dec. 16, 2014</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/128/2537">128 Stat. 2537</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id121e29ab-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id121e29ac-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on 44 U.S. Code, 1964 ed., § 192 (R.S. § 3805; <ref href="/us/act/1895-01-12/ch23/s56">Jan. 12, 1895, ch. 23, § 56</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/28/609">28 Stat. 609</ref>; 1950 Reorg. Plan No. 20, § 1, eff. <date date="1950-05-24">May 24, 1950</date>, 15 F.R. 3178, <ref href="/us/stat/64/1272">64 Stat. 1272</ref>).</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id121e29ad-e3ef-11ef-8e9f-f6e47fd25777"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
